Rating: 0
The key lime juice and zest give this cheesecake an exquisite flavor. The secret to a having a tender crust is to bake the crust only 15 minutes, not 25 minutes. Otherwise, it is too hard to cut and sticks to the pan. Also, members of my gourmet club and I have decided that the cheesecake is better without the tropical dried-fruit chutney. This recipe is one that I will bake again and again for family and friends.

